description: Numbers k such that there exist sequences a_i, b_i in N (i=1,2,3,4) with 0 < a_1 < a_2 < a_3 < a_4 < k, 0 < b_1 < b_2 < b_3 < b_4 < k and a_i != b_j for all i,j = 1,2,3,4, satisfying both Sum_{i=1..4} a_i = Sum_{i=1..4} b_i = 2*k and Product_{i=1..4} sin(a_i * Pi/(2*k)) = Product_{i=1..4} sin(b_i * Pi/(2*k)).
